   <concept id="FAR_19_507" class="- topic/topic concept/concept " xtrc="">
      <title class="- topic/title ">
         <ph class="- topic/ph " props="autonumber">19.507</ph> Solicitation provisions
and contract clauses.</title>
      <conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody ">
         <ol id="d1170e13" class="- topic/ol ">
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d1202e10">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph> [Reserved]</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d1202e15">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph> [Reserved]</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d1202e20">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(c)</ph> The contracting
officer shall insert the clause at <xref href="52.219-6.dita#FAR_52_219_6"
                        base="i1057393"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">52.219-6</xref>, Notice of Total
Small Business Set-Aside, in solicitations and contracts involving
total small business set-asides. This includes multiple-award contracts
when orders may be set aside for any of the small business concerns
identified in <xref href="19.000.dita#FAR_19_000"
                        base="i1101771"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">19.000</xref>(a)(3), as described
in <xref href="8.405-5.dita#FAR_8_405_5"
                        base="i1117805"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">8.405-5</xref> and <xref href="16.505.dita#FAR_16_505"
                        base="i1104008"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">16.505</xref>(b)(2)(i)(F). Use the
clause at <xref href="52.219-6.dita#FAR_52_219_6"
                        base="i1057393"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">52.219-6</xref> with its Alternate
I when including FPI in the competition in accordance with <xref href="19.502-7.dita#FAR_19_502_7"
                        base="i1100890"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">19.502-7</xref>.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d1202e44">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(d)</ph> The contracting
officer shall insert the clause at <xref href="52.219-7.dita#FAR_52_219_7"
                        base="i1057419"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">52.219-7</xref>, Notice of Partial
Small Business Set-Aside, in solicitations and contracts involving
partial small business set-asides. This includes part or parts of
multiple-award contracts, including those described in <xref href="38.101.dita#FAR_38_101"
                        base="i1077300"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">38.101</xref>. Use the clause
at 52.219-7 with its Alternate I when including FPI in the competition
in accordance with <xref href="19.502-7.dita#FAR_19_502_7"
                        base="i1100890"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">19.502-7</xref>.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d1202e58">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(e)</ph>
                  The contracting officer
shall insert the clause at <xref href="52.219-14.dita#FAR_52_219_14"
                        base="i1057730"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">52.219-14</xref>,
Limitations on Subcontracting, in solicitations and contracts—
               </p>
               <ol class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d1202e67">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>For supplies, services, and construction,
if any portion of the requirement is to be set aside for small business
and the contract amount is expected to exceed the simplified acquisition
threshold, and in any solicitations and contracts that are set aside
or awarded on a sole-source basis in accordance with subparts <xref href="Subpart_19.8.dita#FAR_Subpart_19_8"
                              base="i1099848"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">19.8</xref>, <xref href="Subpart_19.13.dita#FAR_Subpart_19_13"
                              base="i1099552"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">19.13</xref>, <xref href="Subpart_19.14.dita#FAR_Subpart_19_14"
                              base="i1099391"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">19.14</xref>, or <xref href="Subpart_19.15.dita#FAR_Subpart_19_15"
                              base="i1099174"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">19.15</xref>, regardless of dollar
value. This includes multiple-award contracts when orders may be
set aside for small business concerns, as described in <xref href="8.405-5.dita#FAR_8_405_5"
                              base="i1117805"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">8.405-5</xref> and <xref href="16.505.dita#FAR_16_505"
                              base="i1104008"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">16.505</xref>(b)(2)(i)(F), and
when orders may be issued directly to a small business concern as described
in <xref href="19.504.dita#FAR_19_504"
                              base="id203CEK0I0HS"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">19.504</xref>(c)(1)(ii). For
contracts that are set aside, the contracting officer shall indicate
in paragraph (f) of the clause whether compliance with the limitations
on subcontracting is required at the contract or order level;</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d1202e94">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>
                        <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Using
the HUBZone price evaluation preference.</i> However, if the prospective
contractor waived the use of the price evaluation preference, or
is an other than small business, do not insert the clause in the
resultant contract.</p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li props="Runin" class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d1202e101">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(f)</ph>
               </p>
               <ol class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d1202e106">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph> The contracting
officer shall insert the clause at <xref href="52.219-13.dita#FAR_52_219_13"
                              base="i1057715"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">52.219-13</xref>, Notice of Set-Aside
of Orders, in all solicitations for multiple-award contracts under
which orders may be set aside for any of the small business concerns
identified in <xref href="19.000.dita#FAR_19_000"
                              base="i1101771"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">19.000</xref>(a)(3), and all
contracts awarded from such solicitations.</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d1202e117">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph> The contracting
officer shall insert the clause at <xref href="52.219-13.dita#FAR_52_219_13"
                              base="i1057715"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">52.219-13</xref> with its Alternate
I in all full and open solicitations and contracts for multiple-award
contracts under which orders will be set aside for any of the small
business concerns identified in <xref href="19.000.dita#FAR_19_000"
                              base="i1101771"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">19.000</xref>(a)(3)
if the conditions in <xref href="19.502-2.dita#FAR_19_502_2"
                              base="i1100762"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">19.502-2</xref> are
met at the time of order set-aside, and the specific program eligibility
requirements, as applicable, are also then met.</p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li props="Runin" class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d1202e131">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(g)</ph>
               </p>
               <ol class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d1202e136">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph> The contracting
officer shall insert the provision at <xref href="52.219-31.dita#FAR_52_219_31"
                              base="id203KF0S062J"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">52.219-31</xref>, Notice of Small
Business Reserve, in solicitations for multiple-award contracts
that have reserves.</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d1202e144">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph> The contracting
officer shall insert the clause at <xref href="52.219-32.dita#FAR_52_219_32"
                              base="id203KG070CVU"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">52.219-32</xref> Orders Issued
Directly Under Small Business Reserves, in solicitations and the
resulting multiple-award contracts that have reserves.</p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li props="Runin" class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d1202e152">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(h)</ph>
               </p>
               <ol class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d1202e157">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph> The contracting officer shall insert the clause at <xref href="52.219-33.dita#FAR_52_219_33"
                              base="id203KG0I04WS"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">52.219-33</xref>, Nonmanufacturer Rule, in solicitations and contracts, including multiple-award contracts, when orders may be set aside for small business concerns as described in <xref href="8.405-5.dita#FAR_8_405_5"
                              base="i1117805"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">8.405-5</xref> and <xref href="16.505.dita#FAR_16_505"
                              base="id203CGK00TBF"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">16.505</xref>(b)(2)(i)(F), and when orders may be issued directly to a small business concern as described in <xref href="19.504.dita#FAR_19_504"
                              base="id203CEK0I0HS"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">19.504</xref>(c)(1)(ii)), when— </p>
                     <ol class="- topic/ol ">
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p class="- topic/p " id="d1202e175">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(i)</ph>the item being
acquired has been assigned a manufacturing or supply NAICS code,
and–</p>
                        </li>
                        <li props="Runin" class="- topic/li ">
                           <p class="- topic/p " id="d1202e180">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(ii)</ph>
                           </p>
                           <ol class="- topic/ol ">
                              <li class="- topic/li ">
                                 <p class="- topic/p " id="d1202e185">
                                    <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(A)</ph>Any portion of the requirement
is to be–</p>
                                 <ol class="- topic/ol ">
                                    <li class="- topic/li ">
                                       <p class="- topic/p " id="d1202e191">
                                          <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>Set aside
for small business and is expected to exceed the simplified acquisition
threshold; or</p>
                                    </li>
                                    <li class="- topic/li ">
                                       <p class="- topic/p " id="d1202e196">
                                          <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>Set aside
or awarded on a sole-source basis in accordance with subparts <xref href="Subpart_19.8.dita#FAR_Subpart_19_8"
                                                base="i1099848"
                                                outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                                                class="- topic/xref ">19.8</xref>, <xref href="Subpart_19.13.dita#FAR_Subpart_19_13"
                                                base="i1099552"
                                                outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                                                class="- topic/xref ">19.13</xref>, <xref href="Subpart_19.14.dita#FAR_Subpart_19_14"
                                                base="i1099391"
                                                outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                                                class="- topic/xref ">19.14</xref>, or <xref href="Subpart_19.15.dita#FAR_Subpart_19_15"
                                                base="i1099174"
                                                outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                                                class="- topic/xref ">19.15</xref>, regardless of dollar
value; or</p>
                                    </li>
                                 </ol>
                              </li>
                              <li class="- topic/li ">
                                 <p class="- topic/p " id="d1202e213">
                                    <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(B)</ph>
                                    <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Using
the HUBZone price evaluation preference.</i> However, if the prospective
contractor waived the use of the price evaluation preference, or
is an other than small business, do not insert the clause in the
resultant contract.</p>
                              </li>
                           </ol>
                        </li>
                     </ol>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d1202e220">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>The contracting
officer shall not insert the clause at <xref href="52.219-33.dita#FAR_52_219_33"
                              base="id203KG0I04WS"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">52.219-33</xref> when the Small
Business Administration has waived the nonmanufacturer rule (see <xref href="19.505.dita#FAR_19_505"
                              base="id203CGK00TBF"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">19.505</xref>(c)(4)).</p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
         </ol>
      </conbody>
   </concept>
</dita>
